        <div class="insight-box">
            <h3>The Convergence Point</h3>
            <p>Regardless of starting argument, all MMT debates funnel into the same underlying disagreements about monetary operations, institutional design, and economic philosophy.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-section">
            <div class="section-title">3. The Recursive Loops (Where Debates Get Stuck)</div>
            <div class="loop-row">
                <div class="node loop" data-type="loop" data-id="inflation-loop">
                    Inflation-Employment Loop<br>
                    <small>NAIRU → Job Guarantee → Make-work → Unemployment costs → Inflation</small>
                </div>
                <div class="node loop" data-type="loop" data-id="consolidation-loop">
                    Treasury-Central Bank Loop<br>
                    <small>Operational unity → Institutional separation → Legal constraints → Operational reality</small>
                </div>
                <div class="node loop" data-type="loop" data-id="japan-loop">
                    Japan Evidence Loop<br>
                    <small>High debt/low inflation → Stagnation concerns → MMT vindication → Japanese denial</small>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-arrow">
            <span>↓ Debates terminate when participants realize... ↓</span>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-section">
            <div class="section-title">4. Terminal Points (How Debates Actually End)</div>
            <div class="terminal-row">
                <div class="node terminal" data-type="terminal" data-id="definitional">
                    Definitional Impasse<br>
                    <small>"We're using different definitions"</small>
                </div>
